Odhiambo returned with the ball to account for late order batsmen Abbas (10), Irfan Ellahi (16) and Singh (0) to further curtail the chase.Sir Ali finally folded for 133 for the loss of 9 wickets in their 20 overs. Man-of-the-match Dhiren Gondaria and Nelson Odhiambo combined to help Kanbis Sports Club reclaim the Nairobi Invitational Cricket League (NICL) Twenty20 title by 28 runs against the rejuvenated Sir Ali Muslim Club in the final staged at Nairobi Gymkhana Sunday. 

Kanbis, who claimed the toss and elected to bat first, conjured up 161 for the loss of six wickets in their allotted 20 overs, thanks largely to Gondaria’s contribution of 41 runs from 38 deliveries which included four fours. 



